<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>JavaScript Math PJH</h2>

<p>Math.floor() used with Math.random() * 101 returns a random integer between 0 and 100 
(both included):</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
Math.floor(Math.random() * 101);
</script>

</body>
